http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Mangalore/Mangalore-University-will-adopt-four-villages-says-Vice-Chancellor/article13980712.ece

Mangalore University will adopt four villages for conducting a survey of what they lack and need, according to K. Byrappa, Vice-Chancellor of the university. Addressing a gathering after inaugurating a media centre at the Kaveri Guest House on the university campus here on Saturday, he said that Konaje, Katipalla and Balepuni-Naringana villages in Mangaluru taluk and Balpa village in Sullia taluk have been chosen for the study.